| Technique | What it does | Why it avoids latches |
|-----------|--------------|-----------------------|
| **`always @(*)`** | Combines all combinational logic into one block | Synthesis treats it as a pure combinational netlist |
| **Default assignments before the `case`** | Every output gets a value regardless of the opcode | No “unassigned” path that would require a latch |
| **Blocking assignments (`=`)** | All outputs are updated in the same evaluation order | No race conditions that could create a latch |
| **Explicit `default` branch** | Covers any opcode that isn’t listed | Guarantees coverage of all 128 opcode values |
| **No `else` or `if` chains that skip assignments** | Every path assigns all outputs | Prevents inferred memory‑like storage |

